{flagdeco|New Zealand}} Centreport [[Wellington]], New Zealand\n* {{flagdeco|Latvia}} Free Port of [[Ventspils]], Latvia\n* {{flagdeco|Spain}} Port of [[Barcelona]], Spain\n* {{flagdeco|US}} Port of [[Virginia]], US\n* {{flagdeco|Italy}} Port of [[Taranto]], Italy\n* {{flagdeco|Australia}} Flinders Port of [[South Australia]], Australia\n* {{flagdeco|Italy}} Port of [[Ancona]], Italy\n* {{flagdeco|Italy}} Port of [[Trieste]], Italy\n* {{flagdeco|Turkey}} Port of [[Izmir]], Turkey\n}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{Noteslist}}\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== References ==\n* {{cite EB9 |mode=cs2 |wstitle=Amoy |volume=1  |ref={{harvid|''EB''|1878}} |page=748 }}.\n* {{cite EB1911 |mode=cs2 |wstitle=Amoy |volume=1 |ref={{harvid|''EB''|1911}} |page=878 }}.\n* {{citation |last=Ouchterlony |first=John |title=The Chinese War  |location=London |year=1844 |publisher=Saunders & Otley |url=https://archive.org/stream/chinesewaraccoun00ouchrich }}.\n* {{citation |last=Pitcher |first=Philip Wilson |url=https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=K8QIAwAAQBAJ&pg=PP2 |title=Fifty Years in Amoy or A History of the Amoy Mission, China |location=New York |year=1893 |publisher=Reformed Church in America |isbn=9785871498194 }}.\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite book|title=Trade and Society, the Amoy Network on the China Coast, 1683\u20131735|first=Chin-Keong|last=Ng|others=|volume=|edition=|year=1983|publisher=NUS Press|url=https://books.google.com/?id=A04Y6rYnlikC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false|isbn=978-9971690694|accessdate=24 April 2014| ref=harv }}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Xiamen}}\n*[http://english.xm.gov.cn/ Xiamen Municipal People's Government]\n*[http://xiamen.chinadaily.com.cn/index.html Xiamen, China \u2013 local news, business, education, trave]\n*[http://govt.chinadaily.com.cn/regional/xiamen/ Xiamen, Fujian province \u2013 Your online guide to government services in China]\n*[http://www.xmenglish.cn/ Xiamen English website powered by Xiamen Daily]\n* [http://www.whatsonxiamen.com/ What's On Xiamen]\n* [http://www.amoymagic.com/ Amoy Magic \u2013 English Guide to Xiamen & Fujian]\n* {{Wikivoyage-inline}}\n* Historic maps\n** [http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/ams/china_city_plans/txu-oclc-6573019.jpg US Army map of Xiamen, 1945]\n** [http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/historical/amoy_environs_1915.jpg Japanese Government Railways map of Xiamen and surrounds, 1915]\n\n{{Xiamen}}\n{{Fujian topics}}\n{{Fujian}}\n{{Metropolitan cities of the People's Republic of China}}\n{{SEZ}}\n{{Foreign trade in Imperial China |state=collapsed}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Xiamen|*]]\n[[Category:Sub-provincial cities in the People's Republic of China]]\n[[Category:Cities in Fujian]]\n[[Category:Treaty of Nanking|Amoy]]\n[[Category:National Forest Cities in China]]\n", "text_old": "{{Redirect|Amoy}}\n{{Redirect|Emng|the medical procedure|Electromyoneurography}}\n{{About|the city in China|other uses}}\n{{stack begin}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = {{raise|0.2em|Xiamen}}\n| official_name                   = <!-- Official name in English if different from 'name' -->\n| native_name                     = {{lower|0.1em|{{nobold|{{lang|zh-hans|\u53a6\u95e8\u5e02}}}}}}\n| other_name                      = Amoy\n| settlement_type                 = [[Prefecture-level city|Prefecture-level]] and [[Sub-provincial city]]\n| motto                           = {{lang|zh-hans|\u6e29\u99a8\u57ce\u5e02\u00b7\u6d77\u4e0a\u82b1\u56ed}} (Comfortable city, oceanfront garden)\n| image_skyline                   = Xiamen newmontage.png\n| imagesize                       = \n| image_caption                   = From top: Xiamen's CBD, [[Xiamen University]], [[Gulangyu]] Island, [[South Putuo Temple]], beach on Gulangyu Island, and [[Haicang Bridge]]\n| image_flag                      = \n| flag_size                       = \n| image_seal                      = \n| seal_size                       = \n| image_shield     